+# =============================================================================
+# backend/.env  — EXAMPLE TEMPLATE  (copy to backend/.env and fill real values)
+# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
+# This template documents every variable the FastAPI backend reads.
+# The real backend/.env is gitignored and MUST be recreated on each deploy.
+# NEVER commit real secrets. Keep real values only in the deployed .env.
+# =============================================================================
+
+# --- Database (REQUIRED) -----------------------------------------------------
+# MongoDB connection string. The backend fails fast if this is missing.
+# Format: mongodb://<user>:<password>@<host>:<port>/<db>
+MONGO_URL=mongodb://<MONGO_USER>:<MONGO_PASSWORD>@<MONGO_HOST>:27017/<MONGO_DB>
+
+# Database name to use (must match the DB in MONGO_URL). e.g. mygenie
+DB_NAME=<MONGO_DB>
+
+# --- Auth (REQUIRED) ---------------------------------------------------------
+# Secret used to sign admin JWTs (HS256). Backend raises on startup if missing.
+# Generate a strong value, e.g.:  openssl rand -hex 32
+JWT_SECRET=<GENERATE_A_LONG_RANDOM_SECRET>
+
+# --- External POS API (REQUIRED) ---------------------------------------------
+# MyGenie POS base URL the backend proxies to (table-config, air-bnb orders,
+# admin POS-token fetch). Backend raises on startup if missing.
+# Example host: https://preprod.mygenie.online/api/v1
+MYGENIE_API_URL=<MYGENIE_POS_BASE_URL>
+
+# --- CORS (OPTIONAL; defaults to "*") ----------------------------------------
+# Comma-separated list of allowed browser origins. Defaults to "*".
+# PRODUCTION: do NOT use "*". Set the real app origins, e.g.:
+#   CORS_ORIGINS=https://app.mygenie.online,https://18march.mygenie.online
+# (multi-tenant subdomains: prefer locking to the *.mygenie.online family)
+CORS_ORIGINS=*
+
+# --- Test-only (OPTIONAL) -----------------------------------------------------
+# Used by backend/tests/* to know which server URL to hit. Not required at runtime.
+# REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=https://<your-app-host>
